EXTENDED OUTLOOK
SUNDAY TO WEDNESDAY
ISSUED BY THE MET OFFICE ON BEHALF OF THE COASTGUARD AND
MARITIME AGENCY AT 112300 UTC
ON SUNDAY EVENING A DEEP AREA OF LOW PRESSURE 985
CENTRED JUST W OF FITZROY WILL SLWY MOV NWARDS TO BE
CENTRED N OF SHANNON 994 BY MIDDAY ON MONDAY. BY THIS
TIME A SECONDARY LOW 976 WILL HAVE FORMED W OF FITZROY.
BY MIDDAY TUESDAY THE INITIAL LOW WILL HAVE FILLED WITH
THE SECONDARY LOW DRIFTING SLWY NWARDS. FURTHER N A RIDGE
OF HIGH PRESSURE CENTRED OVER SCANDINAVIA 1024 WILL
EXTEND WWARDS TOWARDS ICELAND AND REMAIN SLOW MOV BEFORE
DECLINING ON WEDNESDAY. ON SUNDAY EVENING STRG TO GALE
FORCE SE WINDS WILL AFFECT MUCH OF FITZROY SOLE AND
SHANNON. THESE WILL PERSIST OVERNIGHT INTO MONDAY AND
STRENGTHEN TO SEV GALE AT TIMES IN FITZROY. SE GALES WILL
ALSO DEVELOP IN FASTNET DURING MONDAY MORNING. GALES
PERSISTING OVERNIGHT IN TUESDAY BEFORE EASING N OF
FITZROY ON TUESDAY. LATER ON TUESDAY GALE STRENGTH SW
WINDS IN FITZROY WILL MOV NWARDS INTO SOLE AND SHANNON
ALSO AFFECTING FASTNET LUNDY IRISH SEA AND WERN
PLYMOUTH AT TIMES ON WEDNESDAY
